  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Jordan: Insolvency Law Judicial Training</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To develop efficient, scalable and uniform training programme to judges on insolvency law. 2) To develop the capacity of judges dealing with insolvency cases. 3) To set up a sustainable continuous training modality for the judges with a view to strengthening the quality and uniformity of the administration of justice and predictability of court decisions in the insolvency sector.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: The Judicial Council of Jordan (JCJ), the Judicial Institute of Jordan (JIJ) and judges. 
Indirect beneficiaries: The Ministry of Industry, Trade and Supply and the business community.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to further implementation of the Insolvency Law in Jordan by supporting the Judiciary to adopt a sustainable approach for judicial capacity building in insolvency.</narrative>
  </description>
